Without citing evidence, he claimed at the White House coronavirus task force briefing Wednesday that the U.S. is past its peak on new coronavirus cases.
While the total number of cases may be slowing, it's not true for all parts of the country.
"The battle continues, but the data suggests that nationwide, we have passed the peak on new cases," Trump claimed.
